				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">This or That?<a name="68749"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Nov 2 04 9:15 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Im a 64 bard...
<br />
Some times I like to go to Acrylia Caves and kill the lt blue mobs there (sometimes even the dk blue ones). I can pull about 1k in a two hour stint, which for me is pretty good. 
<br />

<br />
Also that is one of the few places I can do what I call &quot;Tank Kiting&quot;. I just walk up to a mob and start whacking on him, playing slow, haste, heal song, dex song. The mobs in AC hit weakly enough for me to take the punishment they are giving (one of the very few places). I am currently at 100pct AA so I do not grow out of the XP here. I actually have a lot of fun doing this and I can do it for as short or long of a time as I want.
<br />

<br />
SO I wish to be more efficient on the dark blues in the inner area. As it is right now I need to stop, mez, and regen my health a couple times per mob in the inner area. If I get an add I can charm but when it breaks I am in a bit of trouble and cant run in that area.
<br />

<br />
To help with this I have gotten the following AAs. (this is not my complete list btw I have a total of 59aa)
<br />
Run3
<br />
Combat Fury 2
<br />
Combat Stability 2
<br />
Harmonious Attack 4 (cant get the 5th until 65)
<br />
Combat Agility 3
<br />

<br />
I use a Battle Drummer's Main Gauche in the main hand 
<br />
And a Copper Hammer of Striking in the off hand (not epiced yet)
<br />

<br />
What should my next purchase be..
<br />
I am debating between 
<br />
Ambidexterity   (ouch 9 aa pts)
<br />
or the Gates Harmonious Attack AAs?
<br />
</span></td>
