				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: This or That?<a name="68773"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Nov 2 04 12:43 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>There is no point using a dagger with a drum mod if you never sings songs with a drum mod?
<br />

<br />
You would see you dps go up significantly if you chanted and instrument swaped while meleing.  Even damage shield/haste/regen/slow can do decent dps.  (if you spend some aa on improving the song strengths)
<br />

<br />
I can't believe at 64 you are going down the path of more mele dps.  You need the deffense yes, but consider the amount of gain .8 to all adds and you have way more dps per aa.  Your healing is much improved, your dots, your scream of pain dd, your damage shield.
<br />

<br />
I think the bdmg is a crap weapon myself.  It is quite low on the mod scale, and the ratio is only ok...but no proc.  Our procs make up a very large part of our dps since the mele portion is so low.  Get 2 decent ratio weapons, preferable with some procs...and then get a ui that lets you easily instrument swap...then raise your singing/IM.  If you ever plan on grouping the IM4, SM4, will be what the guild or group wants from you most.  Instrument swaping can get 3 songs up easily and if you have the lute of howler for 40% and a 36% worn haste that is not too bad...more haste is a wasted song really, since your mele dps will no where come close to a dot thrown in on top.
<br />

<br />
Spending 100aa on all of our mele aa will get you maybe 20dps, a loose guess.  Spending 100aa on IM4, SM4, Critical dot, Critical dd.  Gets you 50ish dps. and 300% more desirablility for groups.  (another guess, but for sure the direction is clear...use reeds spreadsheet to work it out)
<br />

<br />
At some point you just have to come to grips with, Bard mele really does not add up to much overall.  The TDoK is cheap...imagine 2.8 plus .8...3.6 mod to 3 or 4 dots...that is big honking dps vs a 2.0 bdmg.(plus procs from a better mainhand....that 1h blunt big bastard proc weapon is your best bet for now in mainhand.)
<br />

<br />
Moose</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
