				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: This or That?<a name="68847"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Nov 3 04 9:14 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Get Lightning Reflexes 1-4.  Dodge &gt; all.  Everytime a mob misses you, that is 50-2k damage you didn't take.  You might consider swapping Katta's dex song for Nilipus Agi Song.  Agi = more dodge.  EF LDON has a type 3 aug stone that adds 5% dodge also.
<br />

<br />
After you max dodge, get HP, ND3 + PE.  Hp lets you take more hits when dodge doesn't kick in.
<br />

<br />
Fading Memories if you dont have it.
<br />

<br />
IM gives you more regen, and more DS.  DS is DPS.  Everytime the mob hits you, make him pay for it.  SM will do the same thing when using PoV.
<br />

<br />
My standard melee dance mix is Warsong (Haste/DS), PoV (Resists/DS), Muse (Overhaste), Marr (Regen).  I twist Requiem every 3-4 set for slow, and pull with HoS/OoS.  If the mobs don't hit very hard, swap PoV for Nilipus or Shield of Songs.  That 40 point rune eats a surprising amount of damage on light blue mobs.
<br />

<br />
Rappa
<br />
</span></td>
