				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: This or That?<a name="68886"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Nov 3 04 2:44 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>One other method you can use is TDoK in primary and the dex cudgel in secondary.  Have a nice high brass instrument also, like the 2.8 horn.  equip drum, pull with debuff, equip horn slow with the 1 minute DoT/slow, switch to drum and melee while chanting 4 chants (fire/ice/pois/dis - not the magic based one since you are using the 1 minute magic based slow/DoT)  Your TDoK will give you really good damage on your dots, the horn gives your 1 minute dot good damage, and you are still whacking it with the cudgel and having it proc for 600 a pop (less likely to get resisted because you are chanting it!)  Stick the 75 point lifetap prob in the cudgel too.  There is no regen involved here, but you kill fast.  You should see over 100 DPS this way with your AA and level. (I broke 100 DPS this way without a proc in my offhand, just a weapon with an ok ratio at level 64, and I didn't have all the offensive AAs you do at that time)
<br />

<br />
100DPS for 1 minute vs. 50 dps for 2 minutes with some regen going on... I'll take the 1 minute fight, then equip my lute and sit while I regen for the next battle, if needed.  If your regen is lower than the damage you are taking then you will actually have more hps after the 1 minute fight without the regen, than you will after the 2 minute fight with it.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
