				<td colspan="2"><span>Fleet, 
<br />
   I've done what you're doing now, I love tanking stuff instead of kiting, good god if I have to run in one more circle my head is going to explode!
<br />
   I used to have bdmg and troubs mace until I got my epic, then I replaced the mace offhand and did some ldons to get procs, I just recently bought the 100pt proc from EF for about 320 iirc. I only have 14 AAs, and short of spending half my eq time banging out AA points, I don't have a lot of choice on how to drastically increase my dps, the only practical choice is to twist instruments. The dps from warsong of zek with a tdok by itself is impressive, add the pop chants (62,63) with slow song and decent procs, you're in good shape. I think I have an advantage because I have my epic haste bonus but I don't think that's monumental as far as dps goes. I have ca1, cf1, nd1, regen3, run3, and cs1. I tried to get a decent melee balance to marginally offset the fact that I die in less than 2 seconds on bad pulls, but in hindsight I think I should have saved them all for FM. I'm less than 10% from 63 now so I'll be getting FM as soon as possible, after that I plan on doing IM and SM. I honestly don't think that right now AAs are more imprtant than song selection and good twisting technique. I've also found it really helps to have a tradeskill trophy or something else to drastically boost CHA and avoid missed notes. 
<br />
I've done tank kiting very successfully in the following areas:
<br />

<br />
Grieg's End
<br />
Droga
<br />
Nurga
<br />
AC
<br />
Umbral
<br />
KC
<br />
Nadox
<br />
Luggald Caves in Dulak
<br />
Torgian Mines
<br />
Hate's Fury
<br />

<br />
That's the list so far. I recently replaced my BDMG with an ornate stone battlehammer. This increased my straight melee dps slightly, but more importantly, it increased my hps by at least 150 and gave me the mirror proc, which is a real blast to have. I love watching gobbies nuke the sh*t out of themselves in Droga <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-14.gif" border="0" alt="Devil" hspace="2" /><img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-14.gif" border="0" alt="Devil" hspace="2" />
<br />
I have augmented it with a proc from EF and I haven't been happier since. Don't use a wep like bdmg just because it has a mod and you don't have your epic, trust me I was there not too long ago, get a wep with some good solid stats and twist your drum in, you'll <u>really</u> notice the difference. 
<br />
I play the following lineup when I solo tank:
<br />

<br />
Warsong of Zek
<br />
March of the midgets
<br />
Wind of Marr
<br />
Niv's or katta's
<br />

<br />
I always keep Aria of Asceticism memmed to wipe poisons and diseases out with a quick target switch and a few button taps, I think this is essential in places like droga where some of the mobs slow. 
<br />
I know it's weak but I also always have a gate potion on me since I don't have FM yet, my rl friend plays a shammy so he hooks me up with them for free as long as I haul his a$ around bard speed every once in awhile to get him some ingredients/drops. 
<br />

<br />
So anyways let me know if you find any other areas that are fun for this technique, I really enjoy it and it's nice to know there's other folks out there who do too. 
<br />

<br />
Take care man 
