				<td colspan="2"><span>The math is REAL dissapointing to me. I have always FIRMLY believed that all non caster classes should be able to stand toe to toe with a mob that is a few levels lower than them. The method that each class achieves this will vary of course and the general effectiveness will of course vary but it SHOULD be an option..
<br />
I have believed that from Day 1 and continue to believe that to this day. The fact that this game is intentionaly designed to FORCE people to group is irksome to me (and has been since day 1).
<br />

<br />
So being as stuborn as I am ... I have decided to tilt the scales in my favor by grinding out some AAs and getting decent equiptment. And after MUCH work I can now stand toe to toe with some Lt Blue mobs.. yeah!!! And if I kill enough of them ... I will get 1 pct of an AA.
<br />

<br />
But back to the math.
<br />
With my newly aquired Orb of Forgotten Magic and my Copper Hammer I have 30dps .. plus a little bit for my DS (30 per hit I think when not equipted with a brass mod)
<br />

<br />
With a TDOK in hand and singing 4 DOTS (I get the following damage per tick 94, 94, 124, 124) I am at 70 dps.. that is an huge difference. 
<br />

<br />
If I move around a little bit while singing my DOTS I can avoid much of the incoming damage too.... If I run in a rough circle I can all the incoming damage.... Oh , Wait, now I
<br />
m chant kiting.. totally not the point of &quot;tank kiting&quot;. Of course I could just sing my dots and let the mob whack on me.. that might provide some fun. But now all my +atk items are useless ( I am up to +70 or so, ornate + some augs) half my AAs are useless...and the evil designers have won again!!! <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-9.gif" border="0" alt="Crying" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
I just find something satisfying about flailing my arms wildly with weapons and having a mob whacking on me.</span></td>
