<br />

<br />
Why epic? You guessed it, instrument mods. Not only epic has 1.8 instrument mod, it also has 1.8 singing mod. And it saves you the hassle of swapping (I am lazy, I know). With the GoD WarMarch song, Psalm, and epic and IM3, I can put out 81 DS on the mobs when they hit me. With IM4 and the new OOW song, I am guessing it will be well over 100.
<br />

<br />
So if you wanna melee, melee, but increase your mods, will give you more DS (Damage after all), and get LR4 and ID4 ASAP too, so you take less DMG through Dodge. The LDoN thing is +8% Dodge. And HA and Weapon Affinity for more procs, and if you have still more hunger for AAs, get proc crit AAs.
<br />

<br />
That about it. 
<br />

<br />
Fading Memories is 100% fail safe. You only need to remember one thing, stop attack and stop song (I have it built up in a macro), and if mobs don&#180;t see thru invisile (undeads mostly), you are pretty safe. I have used FM in LDoNs with 5-8 mobs all around me and on top of me, and no agro.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"></span></td>
			</tr><tr>
